-@title='middleman-heroku template'

:textile
    Generate a static site with "middleman":http://middlemanapp.com/ and then host it with "heroku":http://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/static-sites-on-heroku. Use "clean urls":clean-urls.

    
    To make your site use:
    * "haml":http://haml-lang.com/ and "textile":http://redcloth.org/hobix.com/textile/
    * "sass":http://sass-lang.com/ and "compass":http://compass-style.org/reference/compass/
    * "coffeescript":http://coffeescript.com and "sprockets":http://middlemanapp.com/guides/coffeescript-sprockets
    * "livereload":http://bit.ly/r0IHMJ (<code>middleman server --livereload</code>)
        
    Then when you are ready, "put the site on heroku":http://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/quickstart:
    * <code>heroku create</code> (the first time)
    * <code>middleman build</code>
    * <code>git add build/*</code> (if you add new pages)
    * <code>git commit</code>
    * <code>git push heroku master</code>